 
'-------------------------------------------------------------- 
'This example is from https://topas.webspace.durham.ac.uk/tutorial_organicriet/
'It shows how to refine an organic structure using distance and angle restraints and restraints to flatten rings
'Later parts of the same tutorial discuss using rigid bodies and z-matrices on the same example
'Data are a short data collection on a Bruker d8 diffractometer witha Ge 111 incident beam monochromator
'-------------------------------------------------------------- 
 
r_wp  7.8724362 r_exp  4.57193677 r_p  6.28416406 r_wp_dash  18.4279758 r_p_dash  20.7413416 r_exp_dash  10.7020925 weighted_Durbin_Watson  0.717081363 gof  1.721904
iters 100000 
chi2_convergence_criteria 0.001 
'do_errors 
 
'-------------------------------------------------------------- 
'Information on datafile etc here 
'-------------------------------------------------------------- 
xdd d8_00796.RAW 
	start_X 4 
	finish_X 50 
	x_calculation_step = Yobs_dx_at(Xo); 
	bkg @  376.021607` -248.985641`  99.1763386` -83.2963296`  86.3209339` -30.7615786` 
	'Cu radiation, Ge(111) monochromator linear psd
	LP_Factor(!th2_monochromator, 27.26) 
	Simple_Axial_Model(axial, 9.87702319`) 
	CuKa1(0.001) 
	Zero_Error(zero, 0.0252331891`) 
 
